{"title":"Digital Service Standard","public_updated_at":"2016-06-29T15:52:18Z","details":{"introduction":"The Digital Service Standard is a set of 18 criteria to help government create and run good digital services.","body":"All public facing transactional services must meet the standard. It’s used by departments and the Government Digital Service to check whether a service is good enough for public use.","points":[{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/understand-user-needs","summary":"Understand user needs. Research to develop a deep knowledge of who the service users are and what that means for the design of the service.","title":"1. Understand user needs"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/do-ongoing-user-research","summary":"Put a plan in place for ongoing user research and usability testing to continuously seek feedback from users to improve the service.\r\n","title":"2. Do ongoing user research"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/make-all-new-source-code-open","summary":"Make all new source code open and reusable, and publish it under appropriate licences (or provide a convincing explanation as to why this can't be done for specific subsets of the source code).","title":"8. Make all new source code open"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/iterate-and-improve-frequently","summary":"Build a service that can be iterated and improved on a frequent basis and make sure that you have the capacity, resources and technical flexibility to do so.","title":"5. Iterate and improve frequently"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/use-open-standards-and-common-platforms","summary":"Use open standards and common government platforms where available.\r\n","title":"9. Use open standards and common platforms"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/have-a-multidisciplinary-team","summary":"Put in place a sustainable multidisciplinary team that can design, build and operate the service, led by a suitably skilled and senior service manager with decision-making responsibility.\r\n","title":"3. Have a multidisciplinary team"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/make-a-plan-for-being-offline","summary":"Make a plan for the event of the digital service being taken temporarily offline.\r\n","title":"11. Make a plan for being offline"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/use-agile-methods","summary":"Build your service using the agile, iterative and user-centred methods set out in the manual.","title":"4. Use agile methods"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/evaluate-tools-and-systems","summary":"Evaluate what tools and systems will be used to build, host, operate and measure the service, and how to procure them.","title":"6. Evaluate tools and systems"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/understand-security-and-privacy-issues","summary":"Evaluate what user data and information the digital service will be providing or storing and address the security level, legal responsibilities, privacy issues and risks associated with the service (consulting with experts where appropriate).","title":"7. Understand security and privacy issues"},{"base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard/test-the-end-to-end-service","summary":"Be able to test the end-to-end service in an environment identical to that of the live version, including on all common browsers and devices, and using dummy accounts and a representative sample of users.","title":"10. Test the end-to-end service"}]},"routes":[{"type":"exact","path":"/service-manual/service-standard"}],"redirects":[],"publishing_app":"service-manual-publisher","rendering_app":"service-manual-frontend","need_ids":[],"phase":"beta","analytics_identifier":null,"document_type":"service_manual_service_standard","schema_name":"service_manual_service_standard","first_published_at":"2016-06-29T14:56:50Z","base_path":"/service-manual/service-standard","description":null,"content_id":"00f693d4-866a-4fe6-a8d6-09cd7db89